&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Checkr&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Checkr is building the data platform to power safe and fair decisions. Over 140,000 companies and millions of people rely on Checkr for AI verification in the moments that matter most: getting a new job, a new place to live, a car ride, childcare, even a date. Customers include Uber, Pennymac, Airbnb, Doordash, Amazon, and Anthropic.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re a team that thrives on solving complex problems with innovative solutions that advance our mission. Checkr is recognized on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.forbes.com/lists/cloud100/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Forbes Cloud 100 2025 List&lt;/a&gt; and is a Y Combinator 2024 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ycombinator.com/blog/yc-top-companies-2024&quot;&gt;Breakthrough Company&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Truework, recently acquired by Checkr, provides access to crucial employment, income information, and asset information needed for mortgage loans, apartment rentals, background checks, and more. We are disrupting a $5B+ industry, dominated by legacy incumbents and outdated processes, with a better product and intense customer focus. Within Checkr, Truework operates independently, allowing rapid iteration while also being able to leverage the strengths and assets from our core business. Think of it like joining a startup within a startup!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a QA Specialist, you will safeguard the integrity of Truework verifications by auditing HR Reports and Outreach workflows for accuracy, completeness, compliance, and professionalism. You’ll apply rulesets used in Report QA (identity/entity matching, data consistency/completeness, correctness), and assess adherence to Smart Outreach cadences across phone, email, and fax. Your work will help to directly improve verifier satisfaction, reduce rework, and support on-time delivery targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audit completed verification reports against Report QA rulesets, validating identity and entity matching, field completeness, internal consistency, and reasonableness of data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute Outreach QA reviews on a randomized sample of manual-source verifications (email, fax, phone, third-party providers), ensuring required actions are logged, follow-ups meet cadence expectations, and communications meet tone and professionalism standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use the Internal Validator findings to confirm required fields are populated (e.g. employment status with corresponding dates), and flag illogical data (e.g. inactive target with missing end date).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document QA outcomes precisely (pass, soft fail, hard fail, warning), citing evidence and rule references to enable rapid fixes and learning feedback loops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Outreach and Transcription team leadership to resolve discrepancies, coach to standard work, and reduce repeat errors over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support SLA and KPI attainment by promptly reviewing queued items and escalating risk on time-sensitive verifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with or interest in QA, operations auditing, or compliance within background screening, VOE/VOI lending, HR operations, or similar data-sensitive environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of the Truework verification workflows, including manual outreach methods and transcription best practices; familiarity with Report QA concepts (rulesets and outcomes).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail orientation with structured note-taking and the ability to cite evidence for each QA finding; strong written communication and professional etiquette.&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Checkr&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Checkr is building the data platform to power safe and fair decisions. Over 140,000 companies and millions of people rely on Checkr for AI verification in the moments that matter most: getting a new job, a new place to live, a car ride, childcare, even a date. Customers include Uber, Pennymac, Airbnb, Doordash, Amazon, and Anthropic.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We’re a team that thrives on solving complex problems with innovative solutions that advance our mission. Checkr is recognized on &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.forbes.com/lists/cloud100/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Forbes Cloud 100 2025 List&lt;/a&gt; and is a Y Combinator 2024 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ycombinator.com/blog/yc-top-companies-2024&quot;&gt;Breakthrough Company&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team/role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Head of Pricing Strategy&lt;/strong&gt; to build our pricing strategy function. Pricing is one of the highest-leverage decisions a company makes, and at Checkr it&#39;s genuinely complex. We have multiple go-to-market motions, a growing portfolio of acquired businesses, thousands of SKUs with complex configuration and packaging permutations, and we’re building new products that serve new use cases. We&#39;re looking for someone to build this function, drive the decisions, and make a measurable impact on how Checkr captures value across its entire product portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own pricing and packaging strategy across all products and go-to-market channels, from high-touch enterprise to self-serve, and drive successful execution across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build pricing models for new and existing products across customer segments, including consumption-based and outcome-based structures that account for customer value and our product economics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run rigorous pricing research, including conjoint analysis, Van Westendorp price sensitivity studies, economic value driver analysis, and willingness-to-pay interviews, to support pricing decisions and build organizational confidence in them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and run pricing experiments; track and analyze price elasticity, cross-price elasticity, packaging performance, and customer purchasing behavior to inform broader rollouts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a pricing strategy function that uses AI-powered research, automated analysis, and modern tooling to operate at a speed and scale that accelerates innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build pricing and packaging architecture that remains coherent and durable as we launch new products, acquire companies, and scale across channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product, Sales, Marketing, Deal Desk, and Go-to-Market leadership to price new offerings and evolve existing ones. Own pricing governance and keep decisions moving at the speed of the business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track competitive pricing dynamics and market trends on an ongoing basis, and surface actionable insights as things evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define pricing KPIs, build the infrastructure to track them, and communicate performance and recommendations clearly to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience, with 5+ years in B2B pricing and packaging across product-led growth and enterprise sales motions. Experience with consumption business models or businesses with real COGS is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with pricing research methodologies: conjoint analysis, Van Westendorp, discrete choice experiments, and customer willingness-to-pay interview

